From: Percival <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 14 May 2026 06:10:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: ath12k: skip unknown WMI direct-buffer modules

Newer QCN9274 firmware (e.g. WLAN.WBE.1.6-01243) advertises direct-buffer
modules with ids beyond the SPECTRAL/CFR pair that this driver knows
about. The current ath12k_wmi_dma_ring_caps treats anything >=
WMI_DIRECT_BUF_MAX as a hard error and returns -EINVAL, which aborts the
entire SERVICE_READY_EXT2 parse. The device then never finishes
initialization and no wiphy/wlan interfaces are registered.

Skip unknown module ids instead of failing the parse. An unused
direct-buffer capability is harmless; bailing out of probe is not.

Tested-on: QCN9274 hw2.0 (GL.iNet Flint 3, IPQ5332) with
WLAN.WBE.1.6-01243-QCAHKSWPL_SILICONZ-1.

Signed-off-by: Percival <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
---
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wmi.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wmi.c
@@ -4717,14 +4717,25 @@ static int ath12k_wmi_dma_ring_caps(stru
 
 	dir_buff_caps = ab->db_caps;
 	for (i = 0; i < dma_caps_parse->n_dma_ring_caps; i++) {
-		if (le32_to_cpu(dma_caps[i].module_id) >= WMI_DIRECT_BUF_MAX) {
-			ath12k_warn(ab, "Invalid module id %d\n",
-				    le32_to_cpu(dma_caps[i].module_id));
-			ret = -EINVAL;
-			goto free_dir_buff;
+		u32 mod_id = le32_to_cpu(dma_caps[i].module_id);
+
+		if (mod_id >= WMI_DIRECT_BUF_MAX) {
+			/*
+			 * Newer QCN9274 firmware (WLAN.WBE.1.6+) advertises
+			 * direct-buffer modules beyond the SPECTRAL/CFR pair
+			 * this driver knows about. Skip them rather than fail
+			 * the whole service-ready-ext2 parse; bailing leaves
+			 * the device half-initialized and no wlan interfaces
+			 * are registered.
+			 */
+			ath12k_dbg(ab, ATH12K_DBG_WMI,
+				   "skipping unknown direct-buffer module id %u\n",
+				   mod_id);
+			dir_buff_caps[i].id = WMI_DIRECT_BUF_MAX;
+			continue;
 		}
 
-		dir_buff_caps[i].id = le32_to_cpu(dma_caps[i].module_id);
+		dir_buff_caps[i].id = mod_id;
 		dir_buff_caps[i].pdev_id =
 			DP_HW2SW_MACID(le32_to_cpu(dma_caps[i].pdev_id));
 		dir_buff_caps[i].min_elem = le32_to_cpu(dma_caps[i].min_elem);
@@ -4733,10 +4744,6 @@ static int ath12k_wmi_dma_ring_caps(stru
 	}
 
 	return 0;
-
-free_dir_buff:
-	ath12k_wmi_free_dbring_caps(ab);
-	return ret;
 }
 
 static void
